English:
The heck're you looking at?! Get a move on, or
kiss your account goodbye.
Chinese:
喂，你看屁哦。
不快點從老子面前消失的話，老子就要獵你的帳號囉！
Korean:
……임마, 뭘 보는 거야
냉큼 안 가면, 네놈의 계정을 사냥해 버린다
German:
Was glotzt du denn so blöd?! Hau ab, sonst kannst
du deinen Account abschreiben.

English:
[k121] didn't work out so hot.
Word spread through EDEN so fast that everyone
was just super careful.
Chinese:
今天的[k121]，成果不怎樣啊……
消息在EDEN裡傳得太厲害，
最近每個人都變得非常小心了。
Korean:
오늘의 [k121], 성과는 별로였네…
EDEN 내에서 너무 소문이 도니
최근에는 모두 경계하고 있고 말이야
German:
Die Idee mit dem [k121] hat nicht so
geklappt. Das spricht sich in EDEN so schnell rum,
dass alle extrem vorsichtig wurden.

English:
I was a Demon Hacker until a little while ago.
Heard they broke up though. It's weird, you'd
think a few would still be around.
Chinese:
我在不久之前還是惡魔亂舞的一員呢。
我是聽說他們解散了，才會跑來看看的……真的耶，人都跑光了。
Korean:
나, 얼마 전까지 데몬즈에 있었거든
해산됐다길래 와 봤더니… 진짜네, 아무도 없어
German:
Ich war bis vor Kurzem bei den Demons. Aber die
sollen sich ja aufgelöst haben. Komisch, dass
nicht wenigstens ein paar dabeibleiben.

English:
Things've... Things've gotten real heavy lately.
I don't like this.
Chinese: 喂，你最近會不會做得有些太過火啊？
Korean: 야, 최근에 너무 지나친 거 아니야?
German:
Hier ist es ... heftig in letzter Zeit.
Das gefällt mir nicht.

English:
Plus that chick kept calling. What is she all
about? Why did she try to help us?
Chinese:
你經常聯絡的女人……她是什麼人？
為什麼她會幫我們這麼多忙啊？
Korean:
자주 연락을 주고받는 여자… 대체 누구야?
왜 이렇게까지 지원을 해 주는 거야
German:
Außerdem hat diese Tussi dauernd angerufen.
Was will die denn? Warum hat sie versucht,
uns zu helfen?

English:
The hell else can I do? I can't go to Jimiken
anymore!
Chinese: 我也不願意啊……吉米肯先生就是堅持要做啊。
Korean: 어쩔 수 없잖아… 지미켄 씨가 말을 안 들으신다고
German:
Was zum Teufel soll ich denn jetzt noch machen?
Zu Jimiken kann ich ja nicht mehr!

English:
What do I do without the Demons?! What do I do
without Jimiken?! Aaaaah--Hey! Get outta my face!
Chinese:
誰知道啊……嗯！？你看屁啊？
不想被我們狩獵就快滾！
Korean:
어쩔 수 없어…, 응!? 이 자식, 뭘 빤히 보는 거야?
사냥당하고 싶지 않으면 빨리 꺼져!
German:
Was mache ich denn ohne die Demons und ohne
Jimiken?! Aaaaaah ... he! Hau ab!

English: *sigh* I'll never rock as hard as Jimiken.
Chinese:
嗯……，
跟吉米肯先生的搖滾吶喊比起來，我還差得遠呢。
Korean:
………으~음
지미켄 씨의 록한 샤우트처럼 되려면 아직 멀었네
German: *Seufz* Ich werde nie so abrocken wie Jimiken.

English: --Wh-what!? Y-you didn't see that, did you!?
Chinese: ……討厭！你看到了？你全部都看到了？
Korean: …으앗!? 보고 있었어!? 전부 다 보고 있었어!?
German: W-Was? D-Das hast du doch nicht etwa gesehen?!

English:
We are everything to Jimiken! More than just his
adoring fans, and fierce supporters, we are his
destined soul mates!
Chinese:
對吉米肯先生來說，我們……
是他最棒的聽眾兼最棒的靈魂伴侶！
Korean:
지미켄 씨에게 있어서, 우리들은…
최고의 오디언스이며, 최강의 소울메이트
입니다…!
German:
Wir bedeuten Jimiken alles! Wir sind nicht nur
treue Fans und engagierte Unterstützer, sondern
Seelenverwandte!

English:
Wherever he goes, we'll follow! And one day, one
glorious day, he'll make us the Official Jimiken
Air-Band Guitarists!
Chinese:
無論天涯海角，我們都會誓死追隨他！
然後總有一天要成為吉米肯‧空氣‧空氣樂團的空氣成員……！
Korean:
어디까지나 따라가겠습니다… 그리고 언젠가
지미켄 에어 에어밴드의 에어 멤버가…!
German:
Wo er auch hingeht, wir werden ihm folgen!
Und eines wunderbaren Tages macht er uns
zu seinen offiziellen Luftgitarristen!
... Und dann rocken wir so richtig ab!
